<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-90-1230 </DOCNO><TEXT>The results of the first successful experiment, where completely functional(fertile) somatic hybrides, combining nuclear genetic substance of speciesrelative to different types and tribes, were obtained, are presented.The results prove the fact, that hybrids of a normal and irradiation-inactivatedsomatic cells are viable, and by genetic constitution hybrides are meroamphidiploids.The conclusion. that irradiation is the effective factor inducing species-specificelimination of the irradiated cell, is made. The present work, thus,verifies usage prospect of cell-engineering technique for genetic substancetransfer between phyllogenetic removed species of plants.</TEXT></DOC>